<h1 id="third-party-projects">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#third-party-projects" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Third Party Projects
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@foreverxmld:matrix.org">Forever</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I released Random 1.2. It completely changes the UI of the app to fit current UI guidelines. You can download it on <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/page.codeberg.foreverxml.Random">Flathub</a>.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2022/02/twig-31/mrzaZPZkvSrkoPLwwLuWNqhh.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@bilelmoussaoui:gnome.org">Bilal Elmoussaoui</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I have released flatpak-vscode 0.0.17</p>
<ul>
<li>New output terminal for less output delay and working terminal colors</li>
<li>New status bar item for current build and run status</li>
<li>New rust-analyzer integration to run runnables within the sandbox</li>
<li>Improved build and runtime terminal integration</li>
<li>Trigger documents portal in activate (May still be problematic when other extensions, like-rust-analyzer, startups earlier)</li>
<li>Display the &ldquo;Flatpak manifest detected&rdquo; dialog only once</li>
</ul>
<p>Huge thanks to SeaDve for most of the changes that landed this release!</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="telegrand">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#telegrand" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Telegrand <a href="https://github.com/melix99/telegrand/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A Telegram client optimized for the GNOME desktop.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@melix99:gnome.org">Marco Melorio</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It&rsquo;s been a while since I last wrote about Telegrand, but the development hasn&rsquo;t been stopped at all! Here&rsquo;s a short list of what&rsquo;s new since the last update:</p>
<ul>
<li>Implemented chats and contacts search</li>
<li>We now show more information in the chat list, like the mention badge and draft message</li>
<li>We now support the photo message type</li>
<li>Added multi account support (thanks to Marcus Behrendt!)</li>
<li>General improvements to the style</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


<h1 id="documentation">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#documentation" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Documentation
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@ebassi:gnome.org">Emmanuele Bassi</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I have added a &ldquo;Getting Started&rdquo; tutorial to the Developer Documentation website; you can follow various lessons to go from the basic GNOME application template in Builder to a working simple text viewer. At the end of the process you&rsquo;ll know how to load and save files asynchronously, how to update your UI in response to changes, and how to save and load settings: <a href="https://developer.gnome.org/documentation/tutorials/beginners/getting_started.html">https://developer.gnome.org/documentation/tutorials/beginners/getting_started.html</a>

