<h3 id="gtk-rs">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gtk-rs" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>gtk-rs <a href="https://gtk-rs.org/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Safe bindings to the Rust language for fundamental libraries from the GNOME stack.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@julianhofer:gnome.org">Julian Hofer</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I&rsquo;ve refactored the gtk4-rs book and touched most chapters during this process. The biggest changes are:</p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="https://gtk-rs.org/gtk4-rs/stable/latest/book/gobject_signals.html">signals</a> chapter includes the new <code>glib::closure_local!</code> macro.</li>
<li>The interface builder chapter has been renamed to <a href="https://gtk-rs.org/gtk4-rs/stable/latest/book/composite_templates.html">composite templates</a></li>
<li>The composite templates chapter dropped the section about<code>gtk::Builder</code> in favor of introducing<code>gio::Resource</code>.</li>
<li>The composite templates chapter app uses the newly introduced support for template callbacks.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://gtk-rs.org/gtk4-rs/stable/latest/book/todo_app_2.html">second todo app</a> chapter now uses automatic resources to add the shortcut window.</li>
<li>The second todo app chapter uses<code>gio::Settings</code> instead of<code>serde_json</code> to save its state.</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


